snippet.textDisplay:
A few years ago, you spoke at one of my company's customer-focused events. You were earlier in the day, not one of the keynotes. I was so excited to see your speech, and every time I asked someone about you, they said "oh, the YouTube person speaking?". Your session was maybe half-full of attendees, but I was there and it was awesome.
I reflected on it the next couple days at the event and I couldn't find ANYONE, at this technology's customer-focused event, where everyone was learning how to better engage with their customers, I couldn't find ANYONE who was excited about your session to just sit down and talk about it and the other people in online media I was so enthralled with. I realized I wasn't among my peers so I left that company a few months later.
